      • getMeasureCount

        int getMeasureCount()
        Get the number of measures in the part. The count is based on the measure numbers, so even if a part has multiple staves its measure count is the largest measure number.
        Returns:
        number of measures in the part. If there is a pickup measure, it is included in the count.

      • getFullMeasureCount

        int getFullMeasureCount()
        Get the number of complete measures.
        Returns:
        the number of measures excluding the pickup measure.

      • getMeasure

        Measure getMeasure(int staffNumber,
                   int measureNumber)
            throws NoSuchElementException
        Returns the measure with the staff and measure number.
        Parameters:
        staffNumber - Number of staff. Is not used when accessing a single staff part.
        measureNumber - the number of the measure
        Returns:
        the measure with measureNumber from the staff with staffNumber
        Throws:
        NoSuchElementException - if there is no staff of measure with the given number in this part
